{"parentUuid":"b22f5cff-720a-4b80-acf1-d3e9db29a627","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/yarikyermilov/src/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en","sessionId":"789c56d5-eaa6-497c-adc2-071e37df3ae0","version":"2.1.70","gitBranch":"main","slug":"fizzy-swimming-lark","type":"progress","data":{"type":"hook_progress","hookEvent":"SessionStart","hookName":"SessionStart:clear","command":"bun \"${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/hooks/skill-activation/scan.js\" || exit 0"},"parentToolUseID":"3d7d44a0-ee9b-4661-9a36-b4f309b151c9","toolUseID":"3d7d44a0-ee9b-4661-9a36-b4f309b151c9","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:44.449Z","uuid":"0397cbeb-35db-49bb-afa0-63fb94d36f82"}
{"parentUuid":"0397cbeb-35db-49bb-afa0-63fb94d36f82","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/yarikyermilov/src/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en","sessionId":"789c56d5-eaa6-497c-adc2-071e37df3ae0","version":"2.1.70","gitBranch":"main","slug":"fizzy-swimming-lark","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Fix IntroSlide Pre-Activated Tool Icons\n\n## Context\n\nThe IntroSlide (\"let's get to know you\") shows AI tool icons that should only light up when the user explicitly types a tool name. Instead, icons appear randomly pre-activated whenever the user navigates to the slide. This is confusing for presenters.\n\n**Root cause:** Two bugs in `Presentation.tsx`:\n\n1. **`getMatchingToolIds` runs on commands from every slide**, not just the IntroSlide. Navigation shortcuts like `\"n\"` (next) match tool keywords via `kw.includes(normalizedInput)` — e.g. `\"n\"` is contained in `\"anthropic\"`, `\"openai\"`, `\"gemini\"`, `\"sourcegraph\"`, `\"github copilot\"`, `\"something\"` — activating claude, codex, amp, gemini, copilot, ??? all at once. This matches exactly the screenshot.\n\n2. **`activatedTools` is never cleared on slide navigation**, so once polluted, tools stay lit whenever the IntroSlide is visited.\n\n## Critical File\n\n- `src/components/Presentation.tsx` — the only file that needs changes\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Fix 1 — Gate tool activation to the IntroSlide only\n\nIn `handleCommand`, wrap the `getMatchingToolIds` call with a guard:\n\n```ts\n// Only activate tools when on the IntroSlide\nif (slides[currentSlide]?.id === 'intro') {\n  const matchingTools = getMatchingToolIds(command);\n  if (matchingTools.length > 0) {\n    setActivatedTools(prev => {\n      const next = new Set(prev);\n      matchingTools.forEach(id => next.add(id));\n      return next;\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Fix 2 — Reset activatedTools when navigating to IntroSlide\n\nIn the existing `useEffect` that resets `slideInteracted` on slide change, also reset `activatedTools` when landing on the intro slide:\n\n```ts\nuseEffect(() => {\n  setSlideInteracted(false);\n  if (slides[currentSlide]?.id === 'intro') {\n    setActivatedTools(new Set());\n  }\n}, [currentSlide]);\n```\n\nThis ensures each time the presenter arrives at the slide, it starts clean.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Navigate to the IntroSlide — all icons should be unlit\n2. Navigate away (type `n`) and back — icons should still be unlit\n3. On the IntroSlide, type `claude` + Enter — only Claude Code highlights\n4. Navigate away and back — icons reset to unlit again\n5. On a non-IntroSlide, type `gemini` + Enter — no tools activate; navigate to IntroSlide — still all unlit\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/yarikyermilov/.claude/projects/-Users-yarikyermilov-src-how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en/cf7798f3-b9e1-468f-ad6c-214de52c0c95.jsonl"},"uuid":"a57db0af-3b15-47d7-8c1b-f7cf9b9cc618","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:20:43.721Z","planContent":"# Plan: Fix IntroSlide Pre-Activated Tool Icons\n\n## Context\n\nThe IntroSlide (\"let's get to know you\") shows AI tool icons that should only light up when the user explicitly types a tool name. Instead, icons appear randomly pre-activated whenever the user navigates to the slide. This is confusing for presenters.\n\n**Root cause:** Two bugs in `Presentation.tsx`:\n\n1. **`getMatchingToolIds` runs on commands from every slide**, not just the IntroSlide. Navigation shortcuts like `\"n\"` (next) match tool keywords via `kw.includes(normalizedInput)` — e.g. `\"n\"` is contained in `\"anthropic\"`, `\"openai\"`, `\"gemini\"`, `\"sourcegraph\"`, `\"github copilot\"`, `\"something\"` — activating claude, codex, amp, gemini, copilot, ??? all at once. This matches exactly the screenshot.\n\n2. **`activatedTools` is never cleared on slide navigation**, so once polluted, tools stay lit whenever the IntroSlide is visited.\n\n## Critical File\n\n- `src/components/Presentation.tsx` — the only file that needs changes\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Fix 1 — Gate tool activation to the IntroSlide only\n\nIn `handleCommand`, wrap the `getMatchingToolIds` call with a guard:\n\n```ts\n// Only activate tools when on the IntroSlide\nif (slides[currentSlide]?.id === 'intro') {\n  const matchingTools = getMatchingToolIds(command);\n  if (matchingTools.length > 0) {\n    setActivatedTools(prev => {\n      const next = new Set(prev);\n      matchingTools.forEach(id => next.add(id));\n      return next;\n    });\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Fix 2 — Reset activatedTools when navigating to IntroSlide\n\nIn the existing `useEffect` that resets `slideInteracted` on slide change, also reset `activatedTools` when landing on the intro slide:\n\n```ts\nuseEffect(() => {\n  setSlideInteracted(false);\n  if (slides[currentSlide]?.id === 'intro') {\n    setActivatedTools(new Set());\n  }\n}, [currentSlide]);\n```\n\nThis ensures each time the presenter arrives at the slide, it starts clean.\n\n## Verification\n\n1. Navigate to the IntroSlide — all icons should be unlit\n2. Navigate away (type `n`) and back — icons should still be unlit\n3. On the IntroSlide, type `claude` + Enter — only Claude Code highlights\n4. Navigate away and back — icons reset to unlit again\n5. On a non-IntroSlide, type `gemini` + Enter — no tools activate; navigate to IntroSlide — still all unlit\n"}
