{"parentUuid":"36be350f-378e-4ee5-887e-b249c879805b","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/yarikyermilov/src/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en","sessionId":"789c56d5-eaa6-497c-adc2-071e37df3ae0","version":"2.1.70","gitBranch":"main","slug":"fizzy-swimming-lark","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J5bgNG68ZkW35aFdMxFh4V","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# CLAUDE.md\n     2→\n     3→## Project Overview\n     4→\n     5→A custom terminal-themed presentation site built with React and TypeScript. Features a Claude Code-inspired aesthetic with command-based navigation. Hosted on GitHub Pages at https://yermilov.github.io/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en\n     6→\n     7→## Tech Stack\n     8→\n     9→- **Runtime**: Bun\n    10→- **Framework**: React 18 + TypeScript\n    11→- **Bundler**: Vite\n    12→- **Syntax Highlighting**: react-syntax-highlighter\n    13→- **Hosting**: GitHub Pages (auto-deployed via GitHub Actions)\n    14→\n    15→## Commands\n    16→\n    17→```bash\n    18→bun install      # Install dependencies (REQUIRED before first `bun run dev`)\n    19→bun run dev      # Start dev server (http://localhost:5173/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en/)\n    20→bun run build    # Build for production\n    21→bun run preview  # Preview production build\n    22→bun run deploy   # Manual deploy to GitHub Pages\n    23→```\n    24→\n    25→## Project Structure\n    26→\n    27→```\n    28→src/\n    29→├── App.tsx                    # Slide definitions\n    30→├── main.tsx                   # React entry point\n    31→├── index.css                  # Global styles & font import\n    32→├── vite-env.d.ts              # Vite type declarations\n    33→├── types/\n    34→│   └── slides.ts              # TypeScript interfaces\n    35→├── hooks/\n    36→│   └── useSlideNavigation.ts  # Navigation state & command parsing\n    37→├── components/\n    38→│   ├── Presentation.tsx       # Main container component\n    39→│   ├── Slide.tsx              # Fullscreen slide wrapper\n    40→│   ├── TerminalInput.tsx      # Command input box\n    41→│   ├── CodeBlock.tsx          # Syntax-highlighted code\n    42→│   ├── SlideProgress.tsx      # Slide counter\n    43→│   └── OnboardingTooltip.tsx  # Navigation help tooltip\n    44→└── styles/\n    45→    ├── theme.css              # CSS design tokens\n    46→    └── terminal.css           # Component styles\n    47→```\n    48→\n    49→## Adding Slides\n    50→\n    51→Edit `src/App.tsx` and add to the `slides` array:\n    52→\n    53→```tsx\n    54→const slides: SlideDefinition[] = [\n    55→  {\n    56→    id: 'unique-id',\n    57→    content: (\n    58→      <>\n    59→        <h2>Slide Title</h2>\n    60→        <p>Slide content here</p>\n    61→        <ul>\n    62→          <li>List items with terminal-style bullets</li>\n    63→        </ul>\n    64→      </>\n    65→    ),\n    66→    notes: 'Optional speaker notes',\n    67→    background: '#custom-color', // Optional\n    68→  },\n    69→  // Add more slides...\n    70→];\n    71→```\n    72→\n    73→### Using Code Blocks\n    74→\n    75→```tsx\n    76→<CodeBlock\n    77→  language=\"typescript\"\n    78→  filename=\"example.ts\"\n    79→  showLineNumbers\n    80→  code={`const hello = \"world\";`}\n    81→/>\n    82→```\n    83→\n    84→### Using Images\n    85→\n    86→Images in `public/` must be imported with `?url` suffix for GitHub Pages compatibility:\n    87→\n    88→```tsx\n    89→import myImage from '/my-image.png?url';\n    90→\n    91→// In slide content:\n    92→<img src={myImage} alt=\"Description\" />\n    93→```\n    94→\n    95→**Important:** Do NOT use direct paths like `src=\"/image.png\"` — they break on GitHub Pages due to the base URL (`/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en`).\n    96→\n    97→### Full-Screen Image Slides\n    98→\n    99→For slides that display a single image filling the available space:\n   100→\n   101→```tsx\n   102→import myImage from '/my-image.png?url';\n   103→\n   104→{\n   105→  id: 'image-slide-id',\n   106→  content: (\n   107→    <div className=\"image-slide\">\n   108→      <img src={myImage} alt=\"Description\" />\n   109→    </div>\n   110→  ),\n   111→}\n   112→```\n   113→\n   114→The `.image-slide` class automatically:\n   115→- Constrains image to viewport (accounts for timer/input bar)\n   116→- Centers the image\n   117→- Applies terminal-themed border and shadow\n   118→- Uses `object-fit: contain` to preserve aspect ratio\n   119→\n   120→### Slide Content Classes\n   121→\n   122→- `h1.hero` - Extra large hero heading\n   123→- `.text-orange`, `.text-green`, `.text-blue` - Accent colors\n   124→- `.text-dim`, `.text-muted` - Dimmed text\n   125→- `.glow-orange`, `.glow-green` - Text glow effects\n   126→\n   127→## Navigation Commands\n   128→\n   129→Type in the input box:\n   130→- `next` or `n` → Next slide\n   131→- `prev`, `back`, `p`, `b` → Previous slide\n   132→- Number (e.g., `3`) → Go to slide 3\n   133→- `first`, `start`, `home` → First slide\n   134→- `last`, `end` → Last slide\n   135→- `reveal` or `r` → Reveal next content stage\n   136→\n   137→Keyboard (when not typing):\n   138→- Arrow keys, Space, PageDown/Up → Navigate\n   139→- Home/End → First/last slide\n   140→\n   141→## Terminal Theme Principles\n   142→\n   143→### Colors (CSS Custom Properties)\n   144→\n   145→```css\n   146→--terminal-bg: #0a0e14          /* Deep black background */\n   147→--terminal-white: #e2e8f0       /* Primary text */\n   148→--terminal-orange: #f0883e      /* Headings, accents (h1) */\n   149→--terminal-green: #7ee787       /* Subheadings (h2), success */\n   150→--terminal-blue: #79c0ff        /* Links, tertiary headings */\n   151→--terminal-purple: #d2a8ff      /* Functions in code */\n   152→--terminal-cyan: #76e4f7        /* Inline code */\n   153→```\n   154→\n   155→### Typography\n   156→\n   157→- **Font**: JetBrains Mono (monospace)\n   158→- **h1**: 4rem (5rem for `.hero`)\n   159→- **h2**: 3rem\n   160→- **h3**: 2.25rem\n   161→- **Body**: 1.5rem\n   162→\n   163→### Visual Effects\n   164→\n   165→- CRT scan lines overlay\n   166→- Subtle noise texture\n   167→- Phosphor text glow on headings\n   168→- Orange focus glow on input\n   169→- Fade-in slide transitions\n   170→\n   171→## Development Guidelines\n   172→\n   173→### IMPORTANT: Use Frontend Design Skill\n   174→\n   175→**For ANY UI edits to this project, always use the `frontend-design` skill.**\n   176→\n   177→This ensures:\n   178→- Consistent terminal aesthetic\n   179→- High-quality, production-grade code\n   180→- Proper use of design tokens\n   181→- Distinctive, non-generic styling\n   182→\n   183→### IMPORTANT: Verify Changes in Browser\n   184→\n   185→**After ANY change to slides, styles, config, or URLs — verify visually using the Chrome extension.**\n   186→\n   187→Workflow:\n   188→1. Make the change\n   189→2. Confirm dev server is running (`bun run dev`)\n   190→3. Use Chrome extension to navigate to `http://localhost:5173/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en/`\n   191→4. Take a screenshot and confirm the change looks correct before declaring done\n   192→\n   193→### Code Style\n   194→\n   195→- TypeScript strict mode\n   196→- Functional React components\n   197→- CSS custom properties for theming\n   198→- Semantic HTML in slides\n   199→\n   200→## Deployment\n   201→\n   202→Automatic deployment on push to `main` via GitHub Actions. The site deploys to the `gh-pages` branch.\n   203→\n   204→## Image Generation\n   205→\n   206→Use the `generate-image` skill for creating slide visuals with Google Gemini 3 Pro.\n   207→\n   208→### Setup\n   209→\n   210→1. Copy `.env.local.example` to `.env.local`\n   211→2. Add your Gemini API key (get one at https://ai.google.dev/)\n   212→3. Run `bun install` to get `@google/genai`\n   213→\n   214→### Usage\n   215→\n   216→Ask Claude to generate images for slides:\n   217→- \"Generate an image of a futuristic terminal interface\"\n   218→- \"Create a minimalist diagram showing code compilation\"\n   219→- \"Design an abstract background for the intro slide\"\n   220→\n   221→### Manual Usage\n   222→\n   223→```bash\n   224→bun --env-file=.env.local .claude/skills/generate-image/scripts/generate.ts \\\n   225→  --prompt \"description\" \\\n   226→  --ratio \"16:9\" \\\n   227→  --output \"filename.png\"\n   228→```\n   229→\n   230→**Options:**\n   231→- `--ratio`: 16:9 (default), 4:3, 1:1, 4:5\n   232→- `--output`: custom filename (auto-generated if omitted)\n   233→\n   234→Generated images are saved to `public/`.\n   235→\n   236→## Troubleshooting\n   237→\n   238→### `bun install` hangs at \"Resolving...\"\n   239→\n   240→**Symptom:** `bun install` hangs indefinitely at \"Resolving...\" or \"Resolved, downloaded and extracted [N]\"\n   241→\n   242→**Root cause:** The `bun.lock` file may contain URLs to a private registry (e.g., Artifactory) that's unreachable from your network.\n   243→\n   244→**Fix:**\n   245→```bash\n   246→rm -rf bun.lock bun.lockb node_modules package-lock.json && bun install\n   247→```\n   248→\n   249→This regenerates the lockfile using the public npm registry.\n   250→\n   251→**How to diagnose:** Check if `bun.lock` contains private registry URLs:\n   252→```bash\n   253→grep -n \"artifactory\\|private\\|internal\" bun.lock\n   254→```\n   255→\n   256→## Git Conventions\n   257→\n   258→- Commit messages: `Add/Update/Fix/Remove [description]`\n   259→- Include co-author footer for AI-assisted commits\n   260→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"uuid":"57f650ee-4eda-4f75-93b6-8be34062f120","timestamp":"2026-03-08T18:32:42.655Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/yarikyermilov/src/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en/CLAUDE.md","content":"# CLAUDE.md\n\n## Project Overview\n\nA custom terminal-themed presentation site built with React and TypeScript. Features a Claude Code-inspired aesthetic with command-based navigation. Hosted on GitHub Pages at https://yermilov.github.io/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Runtime**: Bun\n- **Framework**: React 18 + TypeScript\n- **Bundler**: Vite\n- **Syntax Highlighting**: react-syntax-highlighter\n- **Hosting**: GitHub Pages (auto-deployed via GitHub Actions)\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\nbun install      # Install dependencies (REQUIRED before first `bun run dev`)\nbun run dev      # Start dev server (http://localhost:5173/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en/)\nbun run build    # Build for production\nbun run preview  # Preview production build\nbun run deploy   # Manual deploy to GitHub Pages\n```\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── App.tsx                    # Slide definitions\n├── main.tsx                   # React entry point\n├── index.css                  # Global styles & font import\n├── vite-env.d.ts              # Vite type declarations\n├── types/\n│   └── slides.ts              # TypeScript interfaces\n├── hooks/\n│   └── useSlideNavigation.ts  # Navigation state & command parsing\n├── components/\n│   ├── Presentation.tsx       # Main container component\n│   ├── Slide.tsx              # Fullscreen slide wrapper\n│   ├── TerminalInput.tsx      # Command input box\n│   ├── CodeBlock.tsx          # Syntax-highlighted code\n│   ├── SlideProgress.tsx      # Slide counter\n│   └── OnboardingTooltip.tsx  # Navigation help tooltip\n└── styles/\n    ├── theme.css              # CSS design tokens\n    └── terminal.css           # Component styles\n```\n\n## Adding Slides\n\nEdit `src/App.tsx` and add to the `slides` array:\n\n```tsx\nconst slides: SlideDefinition[] = [\n  {\n    id: 'unique-id',\n    content: (\n      <>\n        <h2>Slide Title</h2>\n        <p>Slide content here</p>\n        <ul>\n          <li>List items with terminal-style bullets</li>\n        </ul>\n      </>\n    ),\n    notes: 'Optional speaker notes',\n    background: '#custom-color', // Optional\n  },\n  // Add more slides...\n];\n```\n\n### Using Code Blocks\n\n```tsx\n<CodeBlock\n  language=\"typescript\"\n  filename=\"example.ts\"\n  showLineNumbers\n  code={`const hello = \"world\";`}\n/>\n```\n\n### Using Images\n\nImages in `public/` must be imported with `?url` suffix for GitHub Pages compatibility:\n\n```tsx\nimport myImage from '/my-image.png?url';\n\n// In slide content:\n<img src={myImage} alt=\"Description\" />\n```\n\n**Important:** Do NOT use direct paths like `src=\"/image.png\"` — they break on GitHub Pages due to the base URL (`/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en`).\n\n### Full-Screen Image Slides\n\nFor slides that display a single image filling the available space:\n\n```tsx\nimport myImage from '/my-image.png?url';\n\n{\n  id: 'image-slide-id',\n  content: (\n    <div className=\"image-slide\">\n      <img src={myImage} alt=\"Description\" />\n    </div>\n  ),\n}\n```\n\nThe `.image-slide` class automatically:\n- Constrains image to viewport (accounts for timer/input bar)\n- Centers the image\n- Applies terminal-themed border and shadow\n- Uses `object-fit: contain` to preserve aspect ratio\n\n### Slide Content Classes\n\n- `h1.hero` - Extra large hero heading\n- `.text-orange`, `.text-green`, `.text-blue` - Accent colors\n- `.text-dim`, `.text-muted` - Dimmed text\n- `.glow-orange`, `.glow-green` - Text glow effects\n\n## Navigation Commands\n\nType in the input box:\n- `next` or `n` → Next slide\n- `prev`, `back`, `p`, `b` → Previous slide\n- Number (e.g., `3`) → Go to slide 3\n- `first`, `start`, `home` → First slide\n- `last`, `end` → Last slide\n- `reveal` or `r` → Reveal next content stage\n\nKeyboard (when not typing):\n- Arrow keys, Space, PageDown/Up → Navigate\n- Home/End → First/last slide\n\n## Terminal Theme Principles\n\n### Colors (CSS Custom Properties)\n\n```css\n--terminal-bg: #0a0e14          /* Deep black background */\n--terminal-white: #e2e8f0       /* Primary text */\n--terminal-orange: #f0883e      /* Headings, accents (h1) */\n--terminal-green: #7ee787       /* Subheadings (h2), success */\n--terminal-blue: #79c0ff        /* Links, tertiary headings */\n--terminal-purple: #d2a8ff      /* Functions in code */\n--terminal-cyan: #76e4f7        /* Inline code */\n```\n\n### Typography\n\n- **Font**: JetBrains Mono (monospace)\n- **h1**: 4rem (5rem for `.hero`)\n- **h2**: 3rem\n- **h3**: 2.25rem\n- **Body**: 1.5rem\n\n### Visual Effects\n\n- CRT scan lines overlay\n- Subtle noise texture\n- Phosphor text glow on headings\n- Orange focus glow on input\n- Fade-in slide transitions\n\n## Development Guidelines\n\n### IMPORTANT: Use Frontend Design Skill\n\n**For ANY UI edits to this project, always use the `frontend-design` skill.**\n\nThis ensures:\n- Consistent terminal aesthetic\n- High-quality, production-grade code\n- Proper use of design tokens\n- Distinctive, non-generic styling\n\n### IMPORTANT: Verify Changes in Browser\n\n**After ANY change to slides, styles, config, or URLs — verify visually using the Chrome extension.**\n\nWorkflow:\n1. Make the change\n2. Confirm dev server is running (`bun run dev`)\n3. Use Chrome extension to navigate to `http://localhost:5173/how-to-make-your-team-ai-first-en/`\n4. Take a screenshot and confirm the change looks correct before declaring done\n\n### Code Style\n\n- TypeScript strict mode\n- Functional React components\n- CSS custom properties for theming\n- Semantic HTML in slides\n\n## Deployment\n\nAutomatic deployment on push to `main` via GitHub Actions. The site deploys to the `gh-pages` branch.\n\n## Image Generation\n\nUse the `generate-image` skill for creating slide visuals with Google Gemini 3 Pro.\n\n### Setup\n\n1. Copy `.env.local.example` to `.env.local`\n2. Add your Gemini API key (get one at https://ai.google.dev/)\n3. Run `bun install` to get `@google/genai`\n\n### Usage\n\nAsk Claude to generate images for slides:\n- \"Generate an image of a futuristic terminal interface\"\n- \"Create a minimalist diagram showing code compilation\"\n- \"Design an abstract background for the intro slide\"\n\n### Manual Usage\n\n```bash\nbun --env-file=.env.local .claude/skills/generate-image/scripts/generate.ts \\\n  --prompt \"description\" \\\n  --ratio \"16:9\" \\\n  --output \"filename.png\"\n```\n\n**Options:**\n- `--ratio`: 16:9 (default), 4:3, 1:1, 4:5\n- `--output`: custom filename (auto-generated if omitted)\n\nGenerated images are saved to `public/`.\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### `bun install` hangs at \"Resolving...\"\n\n**Symptom:** `bun install` hangs indefinitely at \"Resolving...\" or \"Resolved, downloaded and extracted [N]\"\n\n**Root cause:** The `bun.lock` file may contain URLs to a private registry (e.g., Artifactory) that's unreachable from your network.\n\n**Fix:**\n```bash\nrm -rf bun.lock bun.lockb node_modules package-lock.json && bun install\n```\n\nThis regenerates the lockfile using the public npm registry.\n\n**How to diagnose:** Check if `bun.lock` contains private registry URLs:\n```bash\ngrep -n \"artifactory\\|private\\|internal\" bun.lock\n```\n\n## Git Conventions\n\n- Commit messages: `Add/Update/Fix/Remove [description]`\n- Include co-author footer for AI-assisted commits\n","numLines":260,"startLine":1,"totalLines":260}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"36be350f-378e-4ee5-887e-b249c879805b"}
